VCD for a cause
p3
sVnews
p4
VA few years ago, one of his daughters (the youngest) phoned Atmanathan (longtime secretary of M.S.Subbulakshmi and Sadasivam) and entrusted to him the responsibility of releasing a CD of songs composed by her aunt (father&#8217;s brother&#8217;s wife), Visalakshi Natarajan, and rendered by Sathur&#8217;s daughters, Lalitha Santhanam and Bhuvana Rajagopalan.Visalakshi Natarajan&#8217;s family, which has funded the production of the CDs has decided to donate the proceeds/royalty to the construction of Paramacharya&#8217;s Mani Mantapam.The mission has been accomplished and the album is being released today (June 13) at the Narada Gana Sabha Mini Hall.Atmanathan will be releasing the CD. Neyveli Santhanagoplalan will receive the first copy and Dr. R.Ganesh  the second. K.S.Raghunathan (HMV Raghu), who recorded the songs will be the special speaker.Visalakshi Natarajan is in Chennai from Malaysia especially for this occasion and her son Visvanathan Natarajan, Sathur Subramaniam&#8217;s son-in-law, R. Rajagopalan are also participating.The function, which will begin at 6 p.m., will be followed by  an hour&#8217;s vocal concert by the Sathur sisters.The CD contains 13 songs in various ragas. The 14th song on the Mani Mandapam as conceived by the composer is a Ragamalika.S.Neelakantan of Thiruvalangadu  will be present on the happy occasion.His father Thruvalangadu Sundaresa Iyer and Sathur Subramaniam were good friends.The CDs will be available with Lalitha Santhanam (94445 43850) and Bhuvana Rajagopalan (99405 66660) at Rs. 150 per CD.
